[1] Cases in various countries
Asia
---
Sri Lanka
- National. 24 Dec 2018. Sri Lanka sees large decrease in dengue cases in 2018: 48 669 cases with 52 deaths against more than 186 000 cases in 2017.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/sri-lanka-reports-decrease-in-dengue-increase-in-leptospirosis-in-2018-2018/
- National. 8 Jan 2019. A total of 56 people were killed and over 50 000 infected by the dengue virus in Sri Lanka in 2018, the government information department, quoting the Epidemiology Unit. The highest number of dengue cases had been reported from the capital Colombo District with over 10 000 cases. This was followed by over 5600 cases reported from the Gampaha District in the outskirts of Colombo and the Batticaloa District, in eastern Sri Lanka which reported over 4800 cases.
https://newsin.asia/56-people-killed-by-dengue-in-sri-lanka-in-2018/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Sri Lanka: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,144]
[The case numbers in the second report are different from the first with an approximation stated rather than an absolute number- Mod.UBA]

Pakistan
- Punjab (Rawalpindi). 18 Dec 2018. 1917 suspected dengue fever cases visit allied hospitals; 432 were positive results.
https://www.urdupoint.com/en/health/1917-dengue-fever-suspects-visit-allied-hospi-509768.html

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,825]

India
- Punjab (Patiala). 16 Dec 2018. 2325 cases of dengue fever during 2018 in Patiala district, highest in the state.
https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/district-tops-state-with-2-325-dengue-cases/699203.html
- New Delhi. 17 Dec 2018. 4704 cases in 2018, with 4 deaths, including a minor boy; cases continue to rise despite the onset of winter.
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/delhi-dengue-cases-rise-to-4704-as-year-nears-end/articleshow/67128030.cms
- New Delhi. 24 Dec 2018. Domestic-breeding checkers found mosquito breeding in 234 535 households till 22 Dec 2018; 187 210 legal notices have been served for various violations and 25 981 prosecutions initiated in this regard. Dengue cases in Delhi have risen to 2798 in 2018
https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/headlines/300195-2018-2800-dengue-473-malaria-165-chikungunya-cases-in-delhi
- Maharashtra (Nagpur). 17 Dec 2018. Suspected cases testing positive in private hospitals increased to 5045 highest increase in a year for this city. 543 patients detected positive till end of November 2018.
- Goa. 6 Dec 2018. The Mormugao municipal area has witnessed a whopping 387 cases of dengue from January to November 2018. A school student and a child died this year [2018].
https://www.heraldgoa.in/Goa/387-dengue-cases-detected-in-Mormugao-this-year/139744.html

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of India: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,13626]
[The case number of 4704 in the 17 Dec report is much higher than the 24 Dec report mentioning 2798 cases, clearly one of the figures is incorrect or not updated-Mod.UBA]

Oman
- National. 7 Jan 2019. There have been a total of 40 cases of locally transmitted dengue fever from [12 Dec 2018 to 6 Jan 2019] according to the Ministry of Health. 67 cases recorded in 2018, 30 of them imported.
https://timesofoman.com/article/681683/Oman/Health/40-locally-transmitted-dengue-cases-reported-in-Oman
- Muscat. 8 Jan 2019. A major 2-week campaign to combat the spread of _Aedes aegypti_ mosquitoes to control dengue fever cases in Muscat was launched on [Mon 7 Jan 2018]. The Ministry of Health (MoH) is organising this campaign in collaboration with Muscat Municipality under the theme 'Your Cooperation Indicates Your Awareness'.
https://muscatdaily.com/Archive/Oman/Campaign-to-control-breeding-of-dengue-fever-mosquitoes-begins-5co0
- Seeb. 18 Dec 2018. The Ministry of Health (MoH) is conducting an investigation after the detection of a dengue fever case in Seeb. The case is not travel related but due to local transmission, the ministry said. MoH in cooperation with Muscat Municipality is conducting a survey on the presence of _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito responsible for transmitting dengue, yellow fever, Zika disease, and other viral diseases.
https://muscatdaily.com/Archive/Oman/Dengue-fever-case-reported-in-wilayat-of-Seeb-5ce5

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Oman: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,124]

Philippines
- Pangasinan. 29 Dec 2018. Dengue cases total 7777 this year [2018] up from 4653 cases last year (+67 percent) in the entire province from 1 Jan-19 Nov 2018].
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/philippines-dengue-fever-leptospirosis-pangasinan-2018/
- Cebu. 28 Dec 2018. Provincial Health Office recorded 5093 dengue cases from January to the middle of December 2018. The figure is more than 2017's 4914 cases. However, there were fewer deaths this year (25), compared to last year (45).
https://www.sunstar.com.ph/article/1780543/Cebu/Local-News/Dengue-cases-reach-5K-in-Cebu-this-year
- Caraga, Mindanao. 5 Jan 2019. Dengue cases still rising. 22 deaths as of December 2018, with 6788 cases with 473 cases in the Caraga region in December alone.
https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/01/05/dengue-on-the-rise-in-caraga/
- Eastern Visayas. 10 Jan 2019. The Department of Health (DOH) recorded a 106-percent increase in dengue cases -- 9784 with 50 deaths in 2018
https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/01/09/dengue-cases-rise-106-in-eastern-visayas/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of of Philippines: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,64310]

Singapore
- National. 22 Dec 2018. Cases on the rise in Klang worst in Taman Sentosa, especially in areas with low-cost flats. Total for state: 11 131 cases with 4 deaths. Sentosa: 2070 dengue cases as of 8 Dec 2018, Selat Klang (1393), Port Klang (1169), Sungai Kandis (1058).
https://www.thestar.com.my/metro/metro-news/2018/12/25/combating-dengue-a-tough-task-in-klang/
- National. 10 Jan 2019. Over 200 dengue cases were reported in the 1st week of 2019. National Environment Agency (NEA) detected about 40 per cent more _Aedes aegypti_ mosquitoes in December 2018, compared to that in December 2017.
https://www.businessinsider.my/over-200-dengue-cases-were-reported-in-the-first-week-of-2019-here-are-6-things-you-might-not-know-about-the-virus/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Singapore: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,150]

Cambodia
- National. 5 Dec 2019. Cambodia sees 15 233 dengue fever cases in 11 months, killing 16.
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-12/04/c_137650466.htm

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Cambodia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,145]

Thailand
- National. 12 Dec 2018. Thai health officials report from 1 Jan through 10 Dec 2018, 80 065 dengue fever cases have been recorded from all 77 provinces. 107 fatalities have been reported. The top 5 morbidity rates were from Nakornpathom (321.71/100 000 population.) Nakornsawan (258.31/100 000 population.) Nakornsrithamarat (245.96/100 000 population.) Nakornnayok (232.23 / 100,000 population.) Chiengrai (230.04/100 000 population).
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/thailand-dengue-cases-top-80000-measles-cases-rise-22117/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Thailand: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,151]

Taiwan
- National, imported. 21 Dec 2018. The number of imported dengue fever cases in Taiwan that originated in Cambodia has increased sharply this year to 66 compared with eight in 2017, a senior official at the Centers for Disease Control (CDC) said Friday. Citing CDC data valid as of 20 Dec 2018, Chuang said the total number of imported dengue fever cases in Taiwan this year was 330, with the 3 major sources being Cambodia (66), Viet Nam (62), and the Philippines (56). Last year [2017] the number of cases that originated in Viet Nam was 104 and in the Philippines 39.
http://focustaiwan.tw/news/asoc/201812210011.aspx
- Tainan, imported. 9 Jan 2019. 3 dengue fever cases involving 2 Taiwanese businessmen who had recently visited Viet Nam and a Filipino migrant worker confirmed in Tainan, south west Taiwan. They bring to 25 the total number of cases of the disease being imported to the city in 2018. https://menafn.com/1097947132/Imported-cases-of-dengue-fever-hit-southwest-Taiwan

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Taiwan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,193]

- Reunion Island. 2 Jan 2019. 6739 dengue cases confirmed since 1 Jan 2018, with 6 deaths.
https://www.zinfos974.com/6-739-cas-de-dengue-confirmes-depuis-le-1er-janvier-2018_a135735.html [In French trans. Corr.SB]

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of RÃ©union: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,45149]

Pacific
---
New Caledonia. 27 Dec 2019. Health officials on the South Pacific islands of New Caledonia have declared an epidemic of dengue fever after reporting some 100 cases since November [2018]. A dengue epidemic was originally declared on 22 Feb 2018 as cases skyrocketed through the spring and summer months, tapering off during the fall. 1997 dengue cases have been reported since the beginning of 2018 with dengue type 2 accounting for 85 percent of cases. Nearly 200 people required hospitalization and 2 deaths were reported.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/new-caledonia-reports-rise-dengue-fever-88929/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of New Caledonia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,43165]

Palau
- National. 21 Dec 2018. Dengue outbreak situation report 2 (16-20 Dec 2018). There was one confirmed case of dengue fever identified during the reporting period. This brings the total from 1-20 Dec 2018, to 27 cases. In response to the outbreak, the Ministry of Health activated its emergency response team on 7 Dec 2018.
https://reliefweb.int/report/palau/palau-dengue-outbreak-situation-report-2-december-16-20-2018

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Palau: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6253078,519]

- Regional update. 17 Dec 2018. An outbreak of dengue serotype 3 (DENV-3) has recently been declared in Palau following the laboratory confirmation of 2 cases. Both cases have no recent history of overseas travel and this is the 1st time ever that DENV-3 is identified in Palau. - Source: personal communication with country officials on 11 Dec 2018. Additional information of relevance (such as, imported cases with travel history to Pacific Island countries and territories):
- 19 imported cases of dengue (4 cases of DENV-1, 1 case of DENV-2, 7 cases of DENV-4, and 7 cases of dengue serotype unknown) with travel history to Papua New Guinea were reported by Queensland Health (notifiable conditions data) for the period 1 Jan-9 Dec 2018 available at https://www.health.qld.gov.au/publications/clinical-practice/guidelines-procedures/diseases-infection/surveillance/reports/mosquito-borne/mbd-report.pdf.
https://reliefweb.int/map/world/epidemic-and-emerging-disease-alerts-pacific-17-december-2018

Australia
- Overseas acquired cases of dengue notified in Queensland in 2018 year to date
https://www.health.qld.gov.au/publications/clinical-practice/guidelines-procedures/diseases-infection/surveillance/reports/mosquito-borne/mbd-report.pdf

